[17:27] <Voldenet> hm, Tiny::HTTP has very weird assumptions for reusing handles that may not work with default scheduler

[17:27] <Voldenet> As long as you start requests on the same thread, you can reuse the handle

[17:28] <Voldenet> so if you do `my $response = HTTP::Tiny.new.get: 'http://httpbin.org/get'; await Promise.in(1); $response<content>.decode` it might not work

[17:32] <Voldenet> in multithreaded scenarios handle should use `react/supply whenever` syntax for handling concurrency, because then handle can be just a single boring process

[17:32] <Voldenet> that's what Cro does

